DIGEST OF HB 1267 (Updated January 14, 2026 10:37 am - DI 140)
Citations Affected: IC 5-11.
Synopsis: State board of accounts. Provides that the state board of
accounts is subject to applicable professional auditing standards.
Requires the governor to appoint two deputy examiners, one of whom
must be a certified public accountant, and the other of whom must be
either a certified public accountant or an attorney licensed in Indiana.
Effective: Upon passage.
Lehman, Pierce M, Miller D,
Campbell
January 6, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Government and Regulatory
Reform.
January 14, 2026, reported — Do Pass.
